VALUES ('65d32e7f-4dc9-4d0b-934d-6d418d1877b0', 'Which choice completes the text with the most logical transition?', 'Octopuses can change the color and texture of their skin almost instantly. They use this ability to blend into rocks, coral, and sand to avoid predators. ______ some species can also flash bright warning colors to startle an attacker.', NULL, '[{"id":"A","text":"As a result,","is_correct":false,"explanation":"Wrong: flashing warning colors is another use of the skill, not a consequence of camouflage."},{"id":"B","text":"In contrast,","is_correct":false,"explanation":"Wrong: while warning differs from hiding, the sentence chiefly adds a further use rather than opposing the prior one."},{"id":"C","text":"Furthermore,","is_correct":true,"explanation":"Correct: it adds a second use of the color-changing ability to the one already described."},{"id":"D","text":"In conclusion,","is_correct":false,"explanation":"Wrong: ''In conclusion'' signals a summary, but the sentence introduces new information."}]'::jsonb, 'C', 'Step 1 — Identify the first use
The text describes octopuses using color change to {{yellow:blend into rocks, coral, and sand to avoid predators}}.
Step 2 — Choose the additive transition
Because flashing warning colors is a further use of the same ability, ''Furthermore'' adds it.
Distractor analysis:
- A: ''As a result'' marks a consequence, but this is an added ability, not an effect.
- B: ''In contrast'' overstates the opposition; the sentence mainly adds a use.
- D: ''In conclusion'' marks a summary, but new information appears.', 'Is the warning-color sentence a new added use or a result of camouflage?', 'Expression of Ideas', 'Transitions', 'reading_writing', 'expression', 'TRA', NULL, 'easy', false, 'SAT', 'multiple_choice', true, true, 'scholaris_ai', '{"generator":"scholaris_ai_v1","model":"gemma-4-26b-a4b-it","original":true,"explanation_v2":true}'::jsonb, now(), now())
